    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">This activity is based on a 1-stage R134A cycle to cool process streams at -15°C with a capacity of 1 MW. R134A as a working fluid us at -20°C. The compression refrigeration system recirculates 36924 kg/h of R134A. It requires 710 kW for compression, and 1.659 MW for cooling water (the temperature of which increases from 32 to 43°C) to provide 1 MW of cooling. 
References:
Luyben, William L. "Refrigerant selection for different cryogenic temperatures." Computers &amp; Chemical Engineering 126 (2019): 241-248.
</samplingProcedure>
      </representativeness>
